# Test manifest for Mozmill.
# Format:
# <test_type> <test_location> {<options>} {<restrictions>}
# Where:
# <test_type>: mozmill - standard test, run mozmill, load test
#               restart - mozmill restart test, assumes test_location is a directory
#               python  - assumes the test_location is a directory of python files
#                         or a python file which contains a test a la python 
#                         unittest style.
# <test_location>: file of test or directory of tests, if a directory, then mozmill
#                  will start with a -t <dir> parameter, otherwise we'll load
#                  that file specifcially.  Restart tests will error if test_location
#                   is *not* a directory.
# <options>: extra options to specify on the mozmill/mozmill restart command
#             line (profile settings etc etc.
# <restrictions>: specific binary types, interesting restrictions etc. 
#                 Format TBD, probably reftest format style.
mozmill test_unit.js
